think Kaeden asked whether sh is required as the Linux seam. Read do_run: std.process.run with argv — execve lineage, no shell. README documents run/spawn/file I/O/env. sh -c is a convenience for env-prefix, pipes, redirects, compounds. Tree already has shell-free pattern: run ["env" "RYE_ZIG=…" rye …] in parity_ch01 witnesses map. Gaps: no child-environ on run yet; count idiom still shells; mkdir&&build compounds.
obs Direct path is already law; shrinking sh -c is growth of Rishi surface or argv-only composition, not a syscall rewrite.
recommend keep-going pin RYE_ZIG via run ["env" "RYE_ZIG=…" …] without sh — mechanical; Claude before new run-environ or mkdir builtins
